        Carlos's involvement with Pandemonium Productions at age seven marked a significant turning point in his
        performing arts journey. Musical theater proved to be a transformative experience, fostering personal and
        artistic growth and laying the groundwork for future opportunities. His time with Pandemonium Productions
        was prolific, featuring in 25 productions, and he further expanded his experience with a show at St.
        Michael's High School and a youth opera at the Santa Fe Opera. Throughout his theatrical career, Carlos took
        on a variety of leading roles, including iconic characters such as Prince Eric in "The Little Mermaid," Bill
        Sykes in "Oliver," Charlie in "Charlie and the Chocolate Factory," and Birdy in "Bye Bye Birdy." These
        diverse roles showcased his versatility and talent as a young performer, solidifying his passion for the
        stage and setting the stage for a promising future in the performing arts.
    </p>
